itunes:summary:
Ross Patterson, Jarred Taylor, and Dan Hollaway sit down with rock musician Barns Courtney in Austin, Texas to discuss a career on the verge on explosion, how he was so poor that he had to raise Jude Law's baby, his love of 90's music, and why "wheelchair porn" is the ultimate sign of making it as a rock star. We complain all the time how there is a shortage of rockstars in this world, we were lucky the stars aligned to collide with Barns on the verge of superstardom for one of the funniest interviews in show history.
